node.text: I followed these stunning sharks for ages, watching them move in precision following oil coming from the dead whale. Australia is full of wild animals and despite this the only thing most people share with them is proximity. Knowledge, respect and information on dangerous marine life needs to become part of our curriculum in schools and general knowledge for adults. People were surfing near this whale with little concept of the danger and our reaction to shark attacks leads to shark deaths. Ineffective cull and in discriminatory nets plague our wildlife because of our fear. No one is reporting on this whale as a warning for surfers. Download everything you need to know about sharks before surfing with them here. www.surfingguidetosharks.com So lucky to have filmed these amazing creatures descend on this whale. @panamunaproject @projecthiu @wsl @envoy.film

node.text: I followed these stunning sharks for ages, watching them move in precision following oil coming from the dead whale. Australia is full of wild animals and despite this the only thing most people share with them is proximity. Knowledge, respect and information on dangerous marine life needs to become part of our curriculum in schools and general knowledge for adults. People were surfing near this whale with little concept of the danger and our reaction to shark attacks leads to shark deaths. Ineffective cull and in discriminatory nets plague our wildlife because of our fear. No one is reporting on this whale as a warning for surfers. Download everything you need to know about sharks before surfing with them here. www.surfingguidetosharks.com So lucky to have filmed these amazing creatures descend on this whale. @panamunaproject @projecthiu @wsl @envoy.film

😱 Needless To Say, Don’t Try This At Home (Or At Sea Either!) 🦈
Video courtesy of Mike Bartel
What do you do when a Great White wants pets?!
The noise of a shark contains many nerves, as well as a special sensory organ called the Ampullae of Lorenzini, which detects electrical fields. This can lead to a shark enjoying light affection, as this shark shows!
However, it must be stated: DO NOT TRY THIS YOURSELF! Unless you are a veteran diver with a vast amount of experience with these apex predators, you will likely just get your hand bitten off!
It’s far safer to just enjoy the footage instead!
